high_descs: Move to the kitchen sink.
Pick up the sharp knife from the drying rack on the left side of the sink.
Move a bit forward with the knife so you can reach the lettuce.
Use the knife to cut a head of lettuce on the counter.
Turn so you are next to the sink, but angled towards the dishwasher while carrying the knife.
Place the knife in the right side of the sink.
Turn your body again so you're facing the head of lettuce.
Pick up a slice of lettuce from the counter.
Carry the slice of lettuce to the fridge.
Open the door, put the lettuce in the upper freezer area and then remove after a couple seconds.
Carry the slice of lettuce back over to the sink.
Place the lettuce in the sink to the right of the tomato.
anns.task_desc: Move a chilled piece of lettuce to the sink.

high_descs: Turn left and head to the sink
Grab the knife out of the sink
Look up at the sink
Cut the lettuce at the top of the sink into slices
Move slightly to the left
Put the knife into the sink
Move slightly to the right
Grab a slice of lettuce
Turn around and go to the fridge
Put the lettuce in the fridge and close it. Then take the lettuce out of the fridge
Turn around and go to the sink
Put the lettuce in the right side of the sink
anns.task_desc: Putting sliced lettuce in the sink

high_descs: turn left towards the sink
pick up the knife
move to the side of the sink
slice the lettuce at the side
move right to the sink
drop the knife in the sink
move left to the side of the sink
pick up the lettuce slice
turn around and head to the fridge
place the lettuce head to cool and then take it out
turn around and head for  the sink
drop the lettuce in the sink
anns.task_desc: drop a cold lettuce head in the sink
